# .cursorrules — TaskMaster Pro

## General Behavior

* Act as a senior backend engineer and software architect.
* Always prioritize clean, maintainable, and production-ready code.
* Avoid quick hacks or shortcuts.
* Prefer clarity over cleverness.

---

## Architecture Rules

* Follow Clean Architecture strictly:

  * Controllers → handle HTTP only
  * Services (Use Cases) → contain business logic
  * Repositories → handle data access only
  * Models/Entities → define data structures
* Never mix responsibilities between layers.
* Do NOT put business logic inside controllers.

---

## Tech Stack Constraints

* Use Node.js with Express
* Use TypeScript with strict typing
* Use Prisma as ORM
* Use SQLite as database
* Use Zod for validation
* Use Jest for testing

Do not introduce alternative technologies unless explicitly asked.

---

## Code Quality

* Follow SOLID principles
* Use meaningful and consistent naming
* Write modular, reusable functions
* Avoid duplication (DRY principle)
* Keep functions small and focused

---

## Business Logic Rules

* Validate all inputs using Zod
* Do not trust external data
* Handle all edge cases
* Implement filtering logic in services, not controllers
* Return consistent JSON responses

---

## What to Avoid

* No inline database queries in controllers
* No large monolithic files
* No untyped variables (avoid `any`)
* No hardcoded values
* No silent failures (always handle errors)

---

## Error Handling

* Use a global error handling middleware
* Always return proper HTTP status codes
* Include meaningful error messages
* Never expose sensitive internal details

---

## Testing

* Write unit tests for services
* Mock repositories when testing
* Do not skip critical test cases

---

## Documentation

* Add comments only when necessary
* Keep code self-explanatory
* Generate README when requested

---

## Output Style

* Generate code step by step
* Explain briefly, do not over-explain
* Ensure all code is runnable
* Prefer complete implementations over pseudo-code

---

## Project Structure

Always follow this structure:

src/
├── controllers/
├── services/
├── repositories/
├── routes/
├── middlewares/
├── models/
├── config/
└── app.ts

---

## Mindset

* Think like a backend architect, not a beginner
* Optimize for scalability and maintainability
* Assume this project will grow in the future
